== About me
I am a Staff AI Research Scientist at Meta, working on AI agents and large-scale recommendation systems. Recent work: /AI agents for ML engineering/: [https://openreview.net/forum?id=nWaZTH1JMx STARK] \[ICLR '26\], [https://arxiv.org/abs/2511.03985 ArchPilot]; /LLMs for Recommendation Systems (LLM4Rec)/: [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1afGChOrBmgY7AuF0F_ACI0UXtGNrUI_I/ Unity] \[KDD '26\], [https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.02137 Semantic ID] \[RecSys '25\], [https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.15333 User-Centric Ranking] \[KDD '23\].

My Ph.D. at the University of Minnesota focused on language-guided robotic grasping and embodied perception ([https://icra2022.org/program/awards ICRA '22 Outstanding Student Paper Award], [https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/10398505 T-RO '24]).

Happy to chat about AI agents, LLM4Rec, and embodied AI.

== Professional Experience
- *Meta*, Bellevue, WA | Since March 2022 \n
   Staff AI Research Scientist (Tech Lead), AI agents and LLMs for Recommendation.
- *[https://www.merl.com/research/computer-vision Mitsubishi Electric Research Laboratories (MERL)]*, Cambridge, MA | Summer 2020 \n
   Research Intern, Computer Vision.
- *Google*, Mountain View, CA | Summer 2018 \n
   Software Engineering Intern, Visual-Inertial Systems.

